# Source-of-truth loose constraints for cowork's FastAPI server.
#
# This file is the input to `pip-compile`; the generated
# `requirements.txt` next to it is what `pip install -r` actually
# reads inside the Docker build (see cowork/Dockerfile, py-builder
# stage). Customer Snyk Container scans flag any unpinned dep in
# requirements.txt as a risk, so the pinned `==` lockfile is the
# shipped artifact and `requirements.in` carries the human-readable
# bounds.
#
# To regenerate after bumping a bound:
#
#   python3 -m venv /tmp/cowork-pin && \
#   /tmp/cowork-pin/bin/pip install pip-tools && \
#   /tmp/cowork-pin/bin/pip-compile --upgrade --output-file requirements.txt requirements.in
#
# Bound rationale:
#   fastapi          — current line for AsyncIO + Starlette compat.
#   uvicorn[standard]— "standard" pulls httptools + uvloop for prod-
#                      grade async I/O; required for the SSE streaming
#                      endpoints in /v1/conversations.
#   python-multipart — required by FastAPI for `UploadFile` form
#                      parsing on /v1/attachments/upload and
#                      /v1/projects/{name}/files/upload.
#   pydantic         — v2 only; v1 is a hard break for our route
#                      models.
#
# Anton itself is installed separately (see scripts/install-anton.sh)
# from git or local source; do NOT add it here.
fastapi>=0.115.0
uvicorn[standard]>=0.32.0
python-multipart>=0.0.12
pydantic>=2.0.0
